notes: Table 9: Apgar5 convergence with full controls + state trends, births weighted, cluster(state). coef=0.00292, p=0.028, N=1237.
No controls: tests sensitivity to control inclusion. coef=0.00314, p=0.057.
Minimal controls (fertility, obgyn): coef=0.00320, p=0.057.
Demographics only: coef=0.00310, p=0.028.
Health supply only: coef=0.00312, p=0.070.
Tort reform only: coef=0.00309, p=0.050.

Drop MD: coef=0.00330, p=0.018. Slightly stronger without Maryland.
Drop always-treated states: coef=0.00313, p=0.025. Similar to baseline.
Drop small states: coef=0.00310, p=0.047. Similar to baseline.
Drop large states: coef=0.00169, p=0.219. Insignificant; effect driven by larger states.
Trim 1% outliers: coef=0.00157, p=0.041. Smaller magnitude, still significant.
Trim 5% outliers: coef=0.00164, p=0.034. Smaller magnitude, still significant.
Post-1980 sample: coef=0.00227, p=0.054. Borderline significant.
Drop DC: coef=0.00274, p=0.037. Similar to baseline.
Drop late adopters: coef=0.00301, p=0.034. Similar to baseline.
Pre-1995 sample: coef=0.00157, p=0.021. Significant in shorter panel.
Good Apgar convergence: coef=0.00024, p=0.571. Different outcome measure; insignificant.
Neonatal mortality convergence: coef=0.0323, p=0.389. Different outcome measure; insignificant.
Cesarean rate convergence: coef=-0.00271, p=0.913. Different outcome; essentially zero.
Low birthweight convergence: coef=0.00608, p=0.582. Different outcome; insignificant.
Preterm delivery convergence: coef=-0.00720, p=0.646. Different outcome; insignificant.
Neonatal mortality level (not convergence): coef=-0.0000365, p=0.904. Different outcome measure.
Apgar score level (not convergence): coef=0.00199, p=0.893. Different outcome measure.
Good Apgar rate level (not convergence): coef=-0.000153, p=0.730. Different outcome measure.
Good Apgar convergence no controls state+year FE only: coef=0.000827, p=0.023. Different outcome and different spec.
Neonatal convergence no controls state+year FE only: coef=-0.0115, p=0.741. Different outcome and different spec.
HC1 robust SE: same coef=0.00292, p<0.001. Much more significant without clustering.
Conventional SE: same coef=0.00292, p<0.001. Much more significant without clustering.
HC3 robust SE: same coef=0.00292, p<0.001. Much more significant without clustering.
Cluster at year level: same coef=0.00292, p<0.001. Much more significant with year clustering.
Good Apgar convergence with HC1 robust SE: different outcome. coef=0.000241, p=0.517.
Neonatal mortality convergence with HC1 robust SE: different outcome. coef=0.0323, p=0.106.
Unweighted OLS for Apgar5: coef=0.00215, p=0.085. Less significant without birth weights.
Good Apgar unweighted: different outcome. coef=0.000355, p=0.384.
Neonatal mortality unweighted: different outcome. coef=0.0564, p=0.197.
Log transformation of outcome: coef=0.0918, p=0.657. Large SE; insignificant.
Squared outcome: coef=0.000166, p=0.117. Insignificant.
IHS transformation: coef=0.00292, p=0.028. Nearly identical to baseline (IHS approx linear for small values).
Standardized (z-score) outcome: coef=0.323, p=0.028. Identical significance; rescaled coefficient.
OLS no weights no clustering: coef=0.00215, p<0.001. Different estimation but same model.
First differences estimator: coef=0.000531, p=0.283. Insignificant; different identification.
Between estimator (cross-section of state means): coef=-0.000554, p=0.817. Sign reversal; no cross-sectional relationship.
